window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>Not all monsters are make-believe. </b></p> <p>When a badly mutilated body washes up on the shores of Loch Ness, DCI Jack Logan's dream of a quiet life in the Highlands is shattered.&nbsp;</p> <p>While the media speculates wildly about monster attacks, Jack and the Major Investigations Team must act fast to catch the killer before they can strike again.&nbsp;</p> <p>But with Nessie-hunters descending on the area in their dozens, and an old enemy rearing his ugly head, the case could well turn out to be the most challenging of Jack's career.&nbsp;</p> <p>And, if he isn't careful, the last.&nbsp;</p> <p><b>Death and dark humour combine in this fast-paced Tartan noir crime thriller set in the Highlands of Scotland. </b></p> <p>‘DCI Logan is sure to become one of Scotland’s best-loved detectives.’ (Adam Croft)</p>"; 
